     <h1>Press Clipping</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>Rachel Metz: <a title="Wired News: We Don't Need No Stinkin' Login" href="http://www.wired.com/news/infostructure/0,1377,64270,00.html">Wired News: We Don&#8217;t Need No Stinkin&#8217; Login</a></p>

<blockquote>

  <p>There&#8217;s also The New York Times link generator put together by an Illinois teen computer programmer, Aaron Swartz. Swartz&#8217;s page lets bloggers post links to Times articles that can be viewed without having to log in to the site.</p>
  
  <p>So far, he&#8217;s gotten a lot of positive feedback, Swartz said.</p>
  
  <p>&#8220;People say, &#8216;Oh, I use it all the time,&#8217;&#8221; he said.</p>
</blockquote>


